column5: If anyone is interested, I hunt pheasants a few times a week and am usually left with a whole bunch of feathers after they are dressed out. If anyone wants them for tying flies take em, there yours. Pm if you want them, R
I'm in!  Hmmmm, are you ever closer to Toronto?  I'm rarely up near Innisfil...
I would love some too if you ever get South towards the city.
Not down in the City alot, but I will hold on to all feathers from here on in,  pick them up when you have a reason to be north like Ice fishing in a few months. R
